transcript: To the left he saw a sloping descent lit up, and facing it a black knoll that seemed as steep as a wall. On this knoll there was a white patch that Rost6v could not at all make out: was it a glade in the wood lit up by the moon, or some unmelted snow, or some white houses? He even thought something moved on that white spot. "I expect it's snow . . . that spot ... a spot une tache/' he thought. "There now . . . it's not a tache . . . Natasha . . . sister, black eyes . . . Na . . . tasha . . . (
